= Introduction

This is a test document to verify:
- *Syntax highlighting* for R chunks
- _Inline R expressions_
- `Code formatting` with Air

= R Code Chunks

```{r setup}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
x<-1:10
y<-x^2+rnorm(10)
df<-data.frame(x=x,y=y)
```

The dataset has #r[nrow(df)] observations.

```{r analysis}
# This should be formatted by Air
result<-df%>%
filter(x>5)%>%
mutate(z=x+y)%>%
summarize(mean_z=mean(z))
```

= Badly Formatted Code

```{r messy}
for(i in 1:10){
if(i%%2==0){
print(i)
}else{
print("odd")
}}
```

= Math and Links

The formula is $E = mc^2$.

Visit https://github.com/posit-dev/air for Air.

